Eduroam is a great concept with a terrible execution. The whole system is buggy and usually results with organisations just defaulting to using no certificate, making the connection unsecure. Furthemore, the app is so bad. The local search doesn't work, the downloaded/installed profiles break constantly and need removing and redownloading. It DOES work, in the end, after you mess with it for 20 minutes and on the 5th attempt of doing nothing differently. The profile WILL break in < 14 days.

Used to be our school's app to set up eduroam, but over the years it feels like development completely stopped on it. The nearby institutions feature is so unreliable that manual search is the go to. On samsung devices specifically the app loses it's config between each phone firmware update, causing chaos among teachers. On newer phones it's flatout impossible to even set up. If you used this app in the past, use "geteduroam" instead, with how things stand, it's a vast improvement.
